{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868775824,"sessionID":"ses_285f9278affers42EQBy8xMnAS","part":{"id":"prt_d7a070743001iHxBrCvpaxAHOc","messageID":"msg_d7a06eea9001FAHSiRLgmawB66","sessionID":"ses_285f9278affers42EQBy8xMnAS","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-5564de344cdc4af1805f2207f0be728f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-019/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-019/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) |\n8: | Module | `cmd` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Shared CLI Infrastructure (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Create `cmd/internal/cli/version.go` with version constants\n20:   - Define `Version = \"0.1.0\"`\n21:   - Define `GitCommit` (populated at build time)\n22:   - Define `BuildDate` (populated at build time)\n23:   - File: `cmd/internal/cli/version.go`\n24:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/internal/cli`\n25: \n26: - [ ] **T1.2**: Create `cmd/internal/cli/flagset.go` with common flag handling\n27:   - Define `FlagSet` struct for common CLI flags\n28:   - Include `Verbose`, `Kubeconfig`, `Namespace` flags\n29:   - Define `BindFlags(fs *flag.FlagSet)` method\n30:   - File: `cmd/internal/cli/flagset.go`\n31:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/internal/cli`\n32: \n33: - [ ] **T1.3**: Create `cmd/internal/cli/logging.go` with klog initialization\n34:   - Define `InitLogging(verbose bool)` function\n35:   - Call `klog.InitFlags(nil)` and set `logtostderr=true`\n36:   - Set verbose level based on flag\n37:   - File: `cmd/internal/cli/logging.go`\n38:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/internal/cli`\n39: \n40: - [ ] **T1.4**: Create `cmd/internal/cli/signal.go` with signal handling\n41:   - Define `SetupSignalHandler() context.Context`\n42:   - Handle SIGTERM, SIGINT for graceful shutdown\n43:   - Return cancelable context\n44:   - File: `cmd/internal/cli/signal.go`\n45:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/internal/cli`\n46: \n47: ### Phase 2: agentcube CLI Binary (ST-2)\n48: \n49: - [ ] **T2.1**: Create `cmd/agentcube/main.go` skeleton\n50:   - Package: `main`\n51:   - Import path: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/cmd/agentcube`\n52:   - Define `main()` function\n53:   - Setup flag parsing with common flags\n54:   - File: `cmd/agentcube/main.go`\n55:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentcube`\n56: \n57: - [ ] **T2.2**: Implement `--version` flag handling in agentcube\n58:   - Add `-v`, `--version` flag\n59:   - Print version info: `AgentCube CLI version: {Version}, commit: {GitCommit}`\n60:   - Exit 0 after printing version\n61:   - File: `cmd/agentcube/main.go`\n62:   - Verification: `./bin/agentcube --version`\n63: \n64: - [ ] **T2.3**: Implement agentcube subcommand structure\n65:   - Define subcommands: `pack`, `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, `status`\n66:   - Use `flag.NewFlagSet` for each subcommand\n67:   - Print usage help on invalid subcommand\n68:   - File: `cmd/agentcube/main.go`\n69:   - Verification: `./bin/agentcube --help`\n70: \n71: - [ ] **T2.4**: Add agentcube help and usage documentation\n72:   - Define command help text\n73:   - Implement `printUsage()` function\n74:   - Add example usage in help output\n75:   - File: `cmd/agentcube/main.go`\n76:   - Verification: `./bin/agentcube`\n77: \n78: ### Phase 3: agentd Daemon Binary (ST-3)\n79: \n80: - [ ] **T3.1**: Create `cmd/agentd/main.go` skeleton\n81:   - Package: `main`\n82:   - Import path: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/cmd/agentd`\n83:   - Define `main()` function\n84:   - Setup flag parsing\n85:   - File: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n86:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentd`\n87: \n88: - [ ] **T3.2**: Define agentd configuration flags\n89:   - `--port` (int, default 8081): HTTP listening port\n90:   - `--router-url` (string): Router service URL\n91:   - `--workload-manager-url` (string): WorkloadManager URL\n92:   - `--idle-cleanup-interval` (duration, default 1m): Cleanup interval\n93:   - `--idle-timeout` (duration, default 15m): Session idle timeout\n94:   - `--kubeconfig` (string): Kubernetes config path\n95:   - `--namespace` (string, default \"default\"): Kubernetes namespace\n96:   - File: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n97:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentd`\n98: \n99: - [ ] **T3.3**: Initialize agentd dependencies\n100:   - Create Kubernetes client from kubeconfig\n101:   - Initialize Redis/Valkey store client\n102:   - Create `SandboxLifecycleManager` instance\n103:   - Create `IdleCleanupController` instance\n104:   - File: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n105:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentd`\n106: \n107: - [ ] **T3.4**: Implement agentd server startup\n108:   - Call `IdleCleanupController.Start()`\n109:   - Setup signal handler for graceful shutdown\n110:   - Wait for shutdown signal\n111:   - Call `IdleCleanupController.Stop()` on exit\n112:   - File: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n113:   - Verification: `go test ./cmd/agentd -v`\n114: \n115: - [ ] **T3.5**: Add agentd version flag\n116:   - Add `--version` flag\n117:   - Print version and exit\n118:   - File: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n119:   - Verification: `./bin/agentd --version`\n120: \n121: ### Phase 4: agentsandbox Runtime Binary (ST-4)\n122: \n123: - [ ] **T4.1**: Create `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go` skeleton\n124:   - Package: `main`\n125:   - Import path: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/cmd/agentsandbox`\n126:   - Define `main()` function\n127:   - Follow pattern from `cmd/picod/main.go`\n128:   - File: `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go`\n129:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentsandbox`\n130: \n131: - [ ] **T4.2**: Define agentsandbox configuration flags\n132:   - `--port` (int, default 8080): HTTP listening port\n133:   - `--workspace` (string): Workspace directory path\n134:   - `--session-id` (string): Current session ID\n135:   - `--sandbox-id` (string): Sandbox identifier\n136:   - `--entrypoint` (string): Agent entrypoint command\n137:   - File: `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go`\n138:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentsandbox`\n139: \n140: - [ ] **T4.3**: Integrate agentsandbox with picod package\n141:   - Import `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod`\n142:   - Create `picod.Config` from flags\n143:   - Create `picod.NewServer(config)`\n144:   - Call `server.Run(ctx)`\n145:   - File: `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go`\n146:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentsandbox`\n147: \n148: - [ ] **T4.4**: Implement agentsandbox graceful shutdown\n149:   - Setup signal handler (SIGTERM, SIGINT)\n150:   - Pass cancelable context to server\n151:   - Log shutdown message\n152:   - File: `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go`\n153:   - Verification: `go test ./cmd/agentsandbox -v`\n154: \n155: - [ ] **T4.5**: Add agentsandbox version flag\n156:   - Add `--version` flag\n157:   - Print version and exit\n158:   - File: `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go`\n159:   - Verification: `./bin/agentsandbox --version`\n160: \n161: ### Phase 5: agentctl Control Tool Binary (ST-5)\n162: \n163: - [ ] **T5.1**: Create `cmd/agentctl/main.go` skeleton\n164:   - Package: `main`\n165:   - Import path: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/cmd/agentctl`\n166:   - Define `main()` function\n167:   - Setup flag parsing\n168:   - File: `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n169:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentctl`\n170: \n171: - [ ] **T5.2**: Define agentctl global flags\n172:   - `--kubeconfig` (string): Kubernetes config path\n173:   - `--namespace` (string, default \"default\"): Kubernetes namespace\n174:   - `--output` (string, default \"table\"): Output format (table, json, yaml)\n175:   - `--verbose` (bool): Enable verbose output\n176:   - File: `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n177:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentctl`\n178: \n179: - [ ] **T5.3**: Implement agentctl `list` subcommand\n180:   - List all AgentRuntime CRs in namespace\n181:   - Output: name, status, endpoint, age\n182:   - Support table/json/yaml output formats\n183:   - File: `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n184:   - Verification: `./bin/agentctl list --namespace=default`\n185: \n186: - [ ] **T5.4**: Implement agentctl `get` subcommand\n187:   - Get specific AgentRuntime by name\n188:   - Show detailed status information\n189:   - Support json/yaml output\n190:   - File: `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n191:   - Verification: `./bin/agentctl get my-agent`\n192: \n193: - [ ] **T5.5**: Implement agentctl `delete` subcommand\n194:   - Delete AgentRuntime by name\n195:   - Support `--force` flag for immediate deletion\n196:   - Support `--wait` flag to wait for deletion\n197:   - File: `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n198:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentctl`\n199: \n200: - [ ] **T5.6**: Implement agentctl `status` subcommand\n201:   - Check session status for an agent\n202:   - Show active sessions count\n203:   - Show last activity time\n204:   - File: `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n205:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/agentctl`\n206: \n207: - [ ] **T5.7**: Add agentctl version flag and help\n208:   - Add `--version` flag\n209:   - Print version and exit\n210:   - Implement usage help\n211:   - File: `cmd/agentctl/main.go`\n212:   - Verification: `./bin/agentctl --version`\n213: \n214: ### Phase 6: Build Configuration (ST-6)\n215: \n216: - [ ] **T6.1**: Create Makefile with build targets\n217:   - `build-agentcube`: Build agentcube binary\n218:   - `build-agentd`: Build agentd binary\n219:   - `build-agentsandbox`: Build agentsandbox binary\n220:   - `build-agentctl`: Build agentctl binary\n221:   - `build-all`: Build all binaries\n222:   - File: `Makefile`\n223:   - Verification: `make build-all`\n224: \n225: - [ ] **T6.2**: Add ldflags for version injection\n226:   - `-X main.Version=$(VERSION)`\n227:   - `-X main.GitCommit=$(GIT_COMMIT)`\n228:   - `-X main.BuildDate=$(BUILD_DATE)`\n229:   - File: `Makefile`\n230:   - Verification: `make build-agentcube && ./bin/agentcube --version`\n231: \n232: - [ ] **T6.3**: Create Dockerfile for each binary\n233:   - Multi-stage Dockerfile for agentcube\n234:   - Multi-stage Dockerfile for agentd\n235:   - Multi-stage Dockerfile for agentsandbox\n236:   - Multi-stage Dockerfile for agentctl\n237:   - File: `build/Dockerfile.agentcube`, `build/Dockerfile.agentd`, etc.\n238:   - Verification: `docker build -f build/Dockerfile.agentcube -t agentcube .`\n239: \n240: - [ ] **T6.4**: Add install target in Makefile\n241:   - `install`: Copy binaries to `/usr/local/bin`\n242:   - Support `PREFIX` variable for custom install path\n243:   - File: `Makefile`\n244:   - Verification: `make install PREFIX=/tmp/test && /tmp/test/bin/agentcube --version`\n245: \n246: ### Phase 7: Unit Tests (ST-7)\n247: \n248: - [ ] **T7.1**: Test agentcube CLI version output\n249:   - Test: `--version` flag prints correct version format\n250:   - Test: exits with code 0\n251:   - File: `cmd/agentcube/main_test.go`\n252:   - Verification: `go test ./cmd/agentcube -run TestVersion -v`\n253: \n254: - [ ] **T7.2**: Test agentcube CLI help output\n255:   - Test: `--help` prints usage information\n256:   - Test: invalid subcommand shows help\n257:   - File: `cmd/agentcube/main_test.go`\n258:   - Verification: `go test ./cmd/agentcube -run TestHelp -v`\n259: \n260: - [ ] **T7.3**: Test agentd daemon startup\n261:   - Test: flags parsed correctly\n262:   - Test: dependencies initialized\n263:   - Test: server startup succeeds (mocked)\n264:   - File: `cmd/agentd/main_test.go`\n265:   - Verification: `go test ./cmd/agentd -v`\n266: \n267: - [ ] **T7.4**: Test agentsandbox runtime startup\n268:   - Test: flags parsed correctly\n269:   - Test: picod server created\n270:   - Test: graceful shutdown works\n271:   - File: `cmd/agentsandbox/main_test.go`\n272:   - Verification: `go test ./cmd/agentsandbox -v`\n273: \n274: - [ ] **T7.5**: Test agentctl control commands\n275:   - Test: `list` command output format\n276:   - Test: `get` command output format\n277:   - Test: `delete` command with flags\n278:   - File: `cmd/agentctl/main_test.go`\n279:   - Verification: `go test ./cmd/agentctl -v`\n280: \n281: - [ ] **T7.6**: Test signal handling in all binaries\n282:   - Test: SIGTERM triggers graceful shutdown\n283:   - Test: SIGINT triggers graceful shutdown\n284:   - File: `cmd/internal/cli/signal_test.go`\n285:   - Verification: `go test ./cmd/internal/cli -v`\n286: \n287: ### Phase 8: Integration & Validation (ST-8)\n288: \n289: - [ ] **T8.1**: Verify all binaries build successfully\n290:   - `go build ./cmd/agentcube`\n291:   - `go build ./cmd/agentd`\n292:   - `go build ./cmd/agentsandbox`\n293:   - `go build ./cmd/agentctl`\n294:   - File: `cmd/`\n295:   - Verification: `go build ./cmd/...`\n296: \n297: - [ ] **T8.2**: Verify binary names and paths\n298:   - Binaries output to `bin/` directory\n299:   - Names: `agentcube`, `agentd`, `agentsandbox`, `agentctl`\n300:   - File: `Makefile`\n301:   - Verification: `make build-all && ls -la bin/`\n302: \n303: - [ ] **T8.3**: Run all cmd tests with coverage\n304:   - `go test ./cmd/... -v` passes\n305:   - Coverage: >70% for cmd packages\n306:   - File: `cmd/`\n307:   - Verification: `go test ./cmd/... -cover`\n308: \n309: - [ ] **T8.4**: Lint and vet verification\n310:   - `go vet ./cmd/...` passes\n311:   - `golangci-lint run ./cmd/...` passes\n312:   - File: `cmd/`\n313:   - Verification: `go vet ./cmd/... && golangci-lint run ./cmd/...`\n314: \n315: - [ ] **T8.5**: Verify Makefile targets\n316:   - `make build-all` succeeds\n317:   - `make test` succeeds\n318:   - `make install` succeeds\n319:   - File: `Makefile`\n320:   - Verification: `make build-all test`\n321: \n322: ---\n323: \n324: ## Task Dependencies\n325: \n326: ```\n327: T1.1 → T1.2 → T1.3 → T1.4\n328:                     ↓\n329:               T2.1 → T2.2 → T2.3 → T2.4\n330:                     ↓\n331:               T3.1 → T3.2 → T3.3 → T3.4 → T3.5\n332:                     ↓\n333:               T4.1 → T4.2 → T4.3 → T4.4 → T4.5\n334:                     ↓\n335:               T5.1 → T5.2 → T5.3 → T5.4 → T5.5 → T5.6 → T5.7\n336:                     ↓\n337:               T6.1 → T6.2 → T6.3 → T6.4\n338:                     ↓\n339:               T7.1 → T7.2 → T7.3 → T7.4 → T7.5 → T7.6\n340:                     ↓\n341:               T8.1 → T8.2 → T8.3 → T8.4 → T8.5\n342: ```\n343: \n344: ---\n345: \n346: ## Verification Commands\n347: \n348: | Task | Verification Command |\n349: |------|----------------------|\n350: | Build all cmd packages | `go build ./cmd/...` |\n351: | Build agentcube | `go build ./cmd/agentcube` |\n352: | Build agentd | `go build ./cmd/agentd` |\n353: | Build agentsandbox | `go build ./cmd/agentsandbox` |\n354: | Build agentctl | `go build ./cmd/agentctl` |\n355: | Run all tests | `go test ./cmd/... -v` |\n356: | Run with coverage | `go test ./cmd/... -cover` |\n357: | Vet check | `go vet ./cmd/...` |\n358: | Lint check | `golangci-lint run ./cmd/...` |\n359: | Makefile build all | `make build-all` |\n360: | Makefile test | `make test` |\n361: | Version check | `./bin/agentcube --version` |\n362: | Help check | `./bin/agentctl --help` |\n363: \n364: ---\n365: \n366: ## Acceptance Criteria\n367: \n368: - [ ] `cmd/agentcube/main.go` compiles and runs with `--version`\n369: - [ ] `cmd/agentd/main.go` compiles with idle cleanup integration\n370: - [ ] `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go` compiles with picod integration\n371: - [ ] `cmd/agentctl/main.go` compiles with list/get/delete commands\n372: - [ ] All binaries support `--version` flag\n373: - [ ] All binaries support `--help` flag\n374: - [ ] All binaries implement graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT\n375: - [ ] Common CLI infrastructure in `cmd/internal/cli/`\n376: - [ ] Makefile targets for building all binaries\n377: - [ ] ldflags inject version/commit/build date\n378: - [ ] Unit tests for each binary's main entry point\n379: - [ ] `go test ./cmd/... -cover` >70% coverage\n380: - [ ] `go vet ./cmd/...` passes\n381: - [ ] `golangci-lint run ./cmd/...` passes\n382: - [ ] Package structure follows agentcube conventions\n383: \n384: ---\n385: \n386: ## File Changes Summary\n387: \n388: | File | Action | Lines Changed | Description |\n389: |------|--------|---------------|-------------|\n390: | `cmd/internal/cli/version.go` | Create | ~20 | Version constants and build info |\n391: | `cmd/internal/cli/flagset.go` | Create | ~30 | Common flag handling utilities |\n392: | `cmd/internal/cli/logging.go` | Create | ~20 | klog initialization helper |\n393: | `cmd/internal/cli/signal.go` | Create | ~25 | Signal handling for graceful shutdown |\n394: | `cmd/agentcube/main.go` | Create | ~80 | Main CLI binary entry point |\n395: | `cmd/agentcube/main_test.go` | Create | ~50 | Unit tests for agentcube CLI |\n396: | `cmd/agentd/main.go` | Create | ~100 | Agent daemon binary entry point |\n397: | `cmd/agentd/main_test.go` | Create | ~60 | Unit tests for agentd daemon |\n398: | `cmd/agentsandbox/main.go` | Create | ~60 | Sandbox runtime binary entry point |\n399: | `cmd/agentsandbox/main_test.go` | Create | ~40 | Unit tests for agentsandbox runtime |\n400: | `cmd/agentctl/main.go` | Create | ~120 | Control tool binary entry point |\n401: | `cmd/agentctl/main_test.go` | Create | ~80 | Unit tests for agentctl commands |\n402: | `Makefile` | Modify | +40 | Build targets for all binaries |\n403: | `build/Dockerfile.agentcube` | Create | ~25 | Multi-stage Docker build |\n404: | `build/Dockerfile.agentd` | Create | ~25 | Multi-stage Docker build |\n405: | `build/Dockerfile.agentsandbox` | Create | ~25 | Multi-stage Docker build |\n406: | `build/Dockerfile.agentctl` | Create | ~25 | Multi-stage Docker build |\n407: \n408: ---\n409: \n410: ## Implementation Notes\n411: \n412: - **Design completed at Stage ST-3**\n413: - **Reference implementation**: `cmd/picod/main.go` provides pattern for sandbox binary\n414: - **Common patterns**: All binaries use klog for logging, flag for CLI parsing\n415: - **Version injection**: Use ldflags at build time for dynamic version info\n416: - **Integration points**:\n417:   - `pkg/agentd` — IdleCleanupController for agentd\n418:   - `pkg/picod` — Server for agentsandbox runtime\n419:   - `pkg/router` — SessionManager for agentd/agentctl\n420:   - `pkg/workloadmanager` — K8sClient for agentd/agentctl\n421:   - `pkg/store` — Store interface for session state\n422:   - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` — CRD types for agentctl\n423: - **Binary naming**:\n424:   - `agentcube`: Main CLI for agent lifecycle (pack/build/publish/invoke/status)\n425:   - `agentd`: Daemon for idle cleanup and session monitoring\n426:   - `agentsandbox`: Sandbox pod runtime sidecar\n427:   - `agentctl`: Admin control tool for K8s resource management\n428: - **Output format**: agentctl supports table, json, yaml formats\n429: - **Signal handling**: All binaries handle SIGTERM/SIGINT for Kubernetes compatibility\n430: \n431: ---\n432: \n433: ## Implementation Timeline\n434: \n435: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n436: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n437: | Phase 1: Shared CLI Infrastructure | T1.1, T1.2, T1.3, T1.4 | Pending | 0% |\n438: | Phase 2: agentcube CLI Binary | T2.1, T2.2, T2.3, T2.4 | Pending | 0% |\n439: | Phase 3: agentd Daemon Binary | T3.1, T3.2, T3.3, T3.4, T3.5 | Pending | 0% |\n440: | Phase 4: agentsandbox Runtime Binary | T4.1, T4.2, T4.3, T4.4, T4.5 | Pending | 0% |\n441: | Phase 5: agentctl Control Tool Binary | T5.1-T5.7 | Pending | 0% |\n442: | Phase 6: Build Configuration | T6.1, T6.2, T6.3, T6.4 | Pending | 0% |\n443: | Phase 7: Unit Tests | T7.1-T7.6 | Pending | 0% |\n444: | Phase 8: Integration & Validation | T8.1-T8.5 | Pending | 0% |\n445: \n446: **Total Progress: 0% Complete (0/35 tasks)**\n\n(End of file - total 446 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) |\n| Module | `cmd` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Shared CLI Infrastructure (ST-1)\n\n- [ ] **T1.1**: Create `cmd/internal/cli/version.go` with version constants\n  - Define `Version = \"0.1.0\"`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-019/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775868775800,"end":1775868775822}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868775826,"sessionID":"ses_285f9278affers42EQBy8xMnAS","part":{"id":"prt_d7a070c2e001OTc7FysZmrm1qY","messageID":"msg_d7a06eea9001FAHSiRLgmawB66","sessionID":"ses_285f9278affers42EQBy8xMnAS","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-150c878e9bea4be2a4083eaef5f32380","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/agentd` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Core Types & Constants (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Create `pkg/agentd/doc.go` with package documentation\n20:   - Package name: `agentd`\n21:   - Description: Agentd idle cleanup controller for monitoring and cleaning idle agent runtime sessions\n22:   - Verification: `go doc ./pkg/agentd`\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T1.2**: Define default constants in `defaults.go`\n25:   - `DefaultIdleCleanupInterval = 1 * time.Minute`\n26:   - `DefaultIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n27:   - File: `pkg/agentd/defaults.go`\n28:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/agentd`\n29: \n30: - [ ] **T1.3**: Define `IdleCleanupStats` struct for stats retrieval\n31:   - Fields: `Interval time.Duration`, `IdleTimeout time.Duration`, `LastCleanupTime time.Time`\n32:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n33:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/agentd`\n34: \n35: ### Phase 2: IdleCleanupController Struct & Constructor (ST-2)\n36: \n37: - [ ] **T2.1**: Define `IdleCleanupController` struct with all required fields\n38:   - `store Store` — for session state lookup\n39:   - `lifecycleManager *SandboxLifecycleManager` — for sandbox deletion delegation\n40:   - `interval time.Duration` — for cleanup check interval\n41:   - `idleTimeout time.Duration` — for idle threshold\n42:   - `stopCh chan struct{}` — for graceful shutdown signal\n43:   - `wg sync.WaitGroup` — for goroutine synchronization\n44:   - `logger Logger` — for structured logging\n45:   - `idleMu sync.RWMutex` — protects `idleTimeout` for thread-safe access\n46:   - `lastCleanupTime time.Time` — tracks last cleanup cycle\n47:   - `lastCleanupMu sync.RWMutex` — protects `lastCleanupTime`\n48:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n49:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/agentd`\n50: \n51: - [ ] **T2.2**: Implement `NewIdleCleanupController` constructor\n52:   - Signature: `NewIdleCleanupController(store Store, lifecycleManager *SandboxLifecycleManager, interval, idleTimeout time.Duration, logger Logger) *IdleCleanupController`\n53:   - Apply defaults: if `interval == 0`, use `DefaultIdleCleanupInterval`\n54:   - Apply defaults: if `idleTimeout == 0`, use `DefaultIdleTimeout`\n55:   - Initialize `stopCh := make(chan struct{})`\n56:   - Validate non-nil store, lifecycleManager, logger\n57:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n58:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestNewIdleCleanupController -v`\n59: \n60: ### Phase 3: Lifecycle Methods (ST-3)\n61: \n62: - [ ] **T3.1**: Implement `Start()` method\n63:   - Call `ctrl.wg.Add(1)`\n64:   - Launch `go ctrl.runLoop()`\n65:   - Non-blocking, returns immediately\n66:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n67:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_StartStop -v`\n68: \n69: - [ ] **T3.2**: Implement `Stop()` method\n70:   - Call `close(ctrl.stopCh)` to signal shutdown\n71:   - Call `ctrl.wg.Wait()` to block until goroutine completes\n72:   - Returns only after goroutine exits\n73:   - Safe to call multiple times (idempotent via sync.Once or nil check)\n74:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n75:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_StartStop -v`\n76: \n77: - [ ] **T3.3**: Implement `runLoop()` background ticker loop\n78:   - Run in separate goroutine (started by `Start()`)\n79:   - Execute `ctrl.runOnce(context.Background())` immediately on start\n80:   - Create `ticker := time.NewTicker(ctrl.interval)`\n81:   - Loop on `select { <-stopCh, <-ticker.C }`\n82:   - On `stopCh`: log `\"idle cleanup controller stopped\"` and return\n83:   - On `ticker.C`: call `ctrl.runOnce(context.Background())`\n84:   - Defer `ctrl.wg.Done()` and `ticker.Stop()`\n85:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n86:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_StartStop -v`\n87: \n88: ### Phase 4: Core Cleanup Logic (ST-4)\n89: \n90: - [ ] **T4.1**: Implement `runOnce(ctx)` — session listing\n91:   - Call `ctrl.store.ListSessions(ctx)` to get all active sessions\n92:   - Log error if list fails: `\"failed to list sessions\"`\n93:   - Return error if list fails\n94:   - Iterate all sessions for idle check\n95:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n96:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce_ListSessions -v`\n97: \n98: - [ ] **T4.2**: Implement `runOnce(ctx)` — idle status check\n99:   - For each session, check `time.Now().Sub(session.LastActivity)`\n100:   - Skip session if `LastActivity.IsZero() == true` (no activity recorded)\n101:   - Mark session as idle if `duration > ctrl.getIdleTimeout()`\n102:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n103:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce_IdleSession -v`\n104: \n105: - [ ] **T4.3**: Implement `runOnce(ctx)` — cleanup execution\n106:   - For idle sessions: call `ctrl.lifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, session.SessionID)`\n107:   - Pass deletion reason as `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`\n108:   - Handle `NotFoundError`: silently ignore (already deleted), continue\n109:   - Handle other errors: log `\"idle cleanup failed\"` with sessionID and err, continue\n110:   - Log successful cleanup: `\"idle cleanup deleted session\"` with sessionID, idleDuration, reason\n111:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n112:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce_Cleanup -v`\n113: \n114: - [ ] **T4.4**: Implement `runOnce(ctx)` — completion logging\n115:   - Track count of cleaned sessions\n116:   - Update `lastCleanupTime` to `time.Now()` after cycle completes\n117:   - Log: `\"idle cleanup cycle completed\"` with `cleanedCount`\n118:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n119:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce_Completion -v`\n120: \n121: ### Phase 5: Runtime Configuration Methods (ST-5)\n122: \n123: - [ ] **T5.1**: Implement `SetIdleTimeout(timeout)` method\n124:   - Acquire `ctrl.idleMu.Lock()`\n125:   - Update `ctrl.idleTimeout`\n126:   - Release mutex\n127:   - Thread-safe for concurrent access\n128:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n129:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_SetIdleTimeout -v`\n130: \n131: - [ ] **T5.2**: Implement `GetIdleTimeout()` method\n132:   - Acquire `ctrl.idleMu.RLock()`\n133:   - Return current `ctrl.idleTimeout`\n134:   - Release mutex\n135:   - Thread-safe for concurrent reads\n136:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n137:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_GetIdleTimeout -v`\n138: \n139: - [ ] **T5.3**: Implement `GetStats()` stats retrieval method\n140:   - Acquire `ctrl.idleMu.RLock()` and `ctrl.lastCleanupMu.RLock()`\n141:   - Return `IdleCleanupStats{Interval, IdleTimeout, LastCleanupTime}`\n142:   - Release mutexes\n143:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n144:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_GetStats -v`\n145: \n146: ### Phase 6: Concurrent Safety (ST-6)\n147: \n148: - [ ] **T6.1**: Implement thread-safe `idleTimeout` access\n149:   - Add `idleMu sync.RWMutex` to `IdleCleanupController` struct\n150:   - Protect all reads via `getIdleTimeout()` internal method\n151:   - Protect all writes via `SetIdleTimeout()`\n152:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n153:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -race -run TestIdleCleanupController_ConcurrentAccess -v`\n154: \n155: - [ ] **T6.2**: Implement thread-safe `lastCleanupTime` access\n156:   - Add `lastCleanupMu sync.RWMutex` to `IdleCleanupController` struct\n157:   - Protect writes in `runOnce()` via `lastCleanupMu.Lock()`\n158:   - Protect reads in `GetStats()` via `lastCleanupMu.RLock()`\n159:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n160:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -race -run TestIdleCleanupController_ConcurrentAccess -v`\n161: \n162: ### Phase 7: Unit Tests (ST-7)\n163: \n164: - [ ] **T7.1**: Test `NewIdleCleanupController` constructor\n165:   - Test: constructor returns valid instance\n166:   - Test: custom interval and timeout are set correctly\n167:   - Test: default values applied when parameters are zero\n168:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n169:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestNewIdleCleanupController -v`\n170: \n171: - [ ] **T7.2**: Test `Start()` and `Stop()` lifecycle\n172:   - Test: `Start()` launches goroutine\n173:   - Test: `Stop()` completes without hanging\n174:   - Test: goroutine exits cleanly\n175:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n176:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_StartStop -v`\n177: \n178: - [ ] **T7.3**: Test `runOnce()` idle session detection\n179:   - Test: idle session (LastActivity > idleTimeout ago) is cleaned\n180:   - Test: active session (LastActivity < idleTimeout ago) remains\n181:   - Test: session with zero LastActivity is skipped\n182:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n183:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce_IdleSession -v`\n184: \n185: - [ ] **T7.4**: Test `runOnce()` error handling\n186:   - Test: all sessions processed even if some cleanups fail\n187:   - Test: NotFound errors silently ignored\n188:   - Test: other errors logged but don't stop cycle\n189:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n190:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce_ContinueOnError -v`\n191: \n192: - [ ] **T7.5**: Test `SetIdleTimeout()` and `GetIdleTimeout()`\n193:   - Test: `SetIdleTimeout()` updates threshold correctly\n194:   - Test: `GetIdleTimeout()` returns updated value\n195:   - Test: `GetStats()` reflects updated timeout\n196:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n197:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_SetIdleTimeout -v`\n198: \n199: - [ ] **T7.6**: Test concurrent access safety\n200:   - Test: no race conditions on `SetIdleTimeout()` concurrent access\n201:   - Test: no race conditions on `GetStats()` concurrent access\n202:   - Test: no race conditions during `runOnce()` with config changes\n203:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n204:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -race -run TestIdleCleanupController_ConcurrentAccess -v`\n205: \n206: ### Phase 8: Integration & Validation (ST-8)\n207: \n208: - [ ] **T8.1**: Verify Store interface integration\n209:   - `store.ListSessions(ctx)` returns `[]*types.SandboxInfo`\n210:   - Sessions include `SessionID` and `LastActivity` fields\n211:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n212:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_StoreIntegration -v`\n213: \n214: - [ ] **T8.2**: Verify SandboxLifecycleManager integration\n215:   - `lifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sessionID)` handles K8s sandbox CR and store cleanup\n216:   - Deletion reason is `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`\n217:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go`\n218:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_LifecycleIntegration -v`\n219: \n220: - [ ] **T8.3**: All unit tests pass with coverage\n221:   - `go test ./pkg/agentd -v` passes all tests\n222:   - Coverage: >80% for `idle_cleanup.go`\n223:   - No race conditions: `go test ./pkg/agentd -race`\n224:   - File: `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go`\n225:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/agentd -cover -coverprofile=coverage.out && go tool cover -func=coverage.out`\n226: \n227: - [ ] **T8.4**: Lint and build verification\n228:   - `go vet ./pkg/agentd` passes with zero issues\n229:   - `golangci-lint run ./pkg/agentd/...` passes\n230:   - `go build ./pkg/agentd` succeeds\n231:   - File: `pkg/agentd/`\n232:   - Verification: `go vet ./pkg/agentd && golangci-lint run ./pkg/agentd/... && go build ./pkg/agentd`\n233: \n234: ---\n235: \n236: ## Task Dependencies\n237: \n238: ```\n239: T1.1 → T1.2 → T1.3\n240:          ↓\n241:        T2.1 → T2.2\n242:               ↓\n243:        T3.1 → T3.2 → T3.3\n244:               ↓\n245:        T4.1 → T4.2 → T4.3 → T4.4\n246:               ↓\n247:        T5.1 → T5.2 → T5.3\n248:               ↓\n249:        T6.1 → T6.2\n250:               ↓\n251:        T7.1 → T7.2 → T7.3 → T7.4 → T7.5 → T7.6\n252:               ↓\n253:        T8.1 → T8.2 → T8.3 → T8.4\n254: ```\n255: \n256: ---\n257: \n258: ## Verification Commands\n259: \n260: | Task | Verification Command |\n261: |------|----------------------|\n262: | All tests | `go test ./pkg/agentd -v` |\n263: | Constructor tests | `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestNewIdleCleanupController -v` |\n264: | Lifecycle tests | `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_StartStop -v` |\n265: | Cleanup tests | `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_runOnce -v` |\n266: | Config tests | `go test ./pkg/agentd -run TestIdleCleanupController_SetIdleTimeout -v` |\n267: | Concurrent safety | `go test ./pkg/agentd -race -run TestIdleCleanupController_ConcurrentAccess -v` |\n268: | Test coverage | `go test ./pkg/agentd -cover -coverprofile=coverage.out && go tool cover -func=coverage.out \\| grep idle_cleanup` |\n269: | Build verification | `go build ./pkg/agentd` |\n270: | Lint check | `golangci-lint run ./pkg/agentd/...` |\n271: | Vet check | `go vet ./pkg/agentd` |\n272: \n273: ---\n274: \n275: ## Acceptance Criteria\n276: \n277: - [ ] `IdleCleanupController` struct defined with all required fields\n278: - [ ] `NewIdleCleanupController` constructor with default fallbacks\n279: - [ ] `Start()` launches background goroutine\n280: - [ ] `Stop()` signals shutdown and waits for completion\n281: - [ ] `runLoop()` uses ticker for periodic execution\n282: - [ ] `runOnce()` checks session idle status via `LastActivity`\n283: - [ ] Sessions with zero `LastActivity` skipped\n284: - [ ] Idle sessions trigger `DeleteSandbox` delegation\n285: - [ ] NotFound errors silently ignored\n286: - [ ] Deletion errors logged but don't stop cycle\n287: - [ ] `SetIdleTimeout()` runtime configuration supported\n288: - [ ] `GetIdleTimeout()` returns current timeout\n289: - [ ] `GetStats()` returns current configuration and last cleanup time\n290: - [ ] Default constants defined: `DefaultIdleCleanupInterval=1m`, `DefaultIdleTimeout=15m`\n291: - [ ] Store `ListSessions()` method used for session lookup\n292: - [ ] `SandboxLifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox()` used for cleanup\n293: - [ ] `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout` logged for observability\n294: - [ ] Unit tests cover idle/active/zero scenarios\n295: - [ ] Unit tests cover Start/Stop lifecycle\n296: - [ ] Package structure follows agentcube conventions\n297: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n298: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n299: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n300: \n301: ---\n302: \n303: ## File Changes Summary\n304: \n305: | File | Action | Lines Changed | Description |\n306: |------|--------|---------------|-------------|\n307: | `pkg/agentd/doc.go` | Create | ~10 | Package documentation for agentd module |\n308: | `pkg/agentd/defaults.go` | Create | ~15 | `DefaultIdleCleanupInterval`, `DefaultIdleTimeout` constants |\n309: | `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go` | Create | ~150 | `IdleCleanupController`, `NewIdleCleanupController`, `Start`, `Stop`, `runLoop`, `runOnce`, `SetIdleTimeout`, `GetIdleTimeout`, `GetStats`, `getIdleTimeout`, `IdleCleanupStats` |\n310: | `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go` | Create | ~350 | Comprehensive unit tests (6 test groups, ~15 test cases) |\n311: \n312: ---\n313: \n314: ## Implementation Notes\n315: \n316: - **Design completed at Stage ST-3**\n317: - **Reference implementation**: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` provides similar pattern\n318: - **Thread-safe implementation**: Use `sync.RWMutex` for `idleTimeout` and `lastCleanupTime` fields\n319: - **Graceful degradation**: Cleanup continues processing even if individual deletions fail\n320: - **Immediate execution**: First cleanup runs immediately on `Start()`, then periodic via ticker\n321: - **Integration points**:\n322:   - `pkg/workloadmanager` — `SandboxLifecycleManager`, `Store`, `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`, `Logger`\n323:   - `pkg/common/types` — `SandboxInfo` struct with `LastActivity` field\n324: - **Key differences from GarbageCollector**:\n325:   - Uses `ListSessions()` instead of `ListExpiredSandboxes()`/`ListInactiveSandboxes()`\n326:   - Filters idle sessions client-side based on `LastActivity` comparison\n327:   - No batch size limit (processes all sessions)\n328:   - Tracks `LastCleanupTime` for observability\n329: \n330: ---\n331: \n332: ## Implementation Timeline\n333: \n334: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n335: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n336: | Phase 1: Core Types & Constants | T1.1, T1.2, T1.3 | Pending | 0% |\n337: | Phase 2: Struct & Constructor | T2.1, T2.2 | Pending | 0% |\n338: | Phase 3: Lifecycle Methods | T3.1, T3.2, T3.3 | Pending | 0% |\n339: | Phase 4: Core Cleanup Logic | T4.1, T4.2, T4.3, T4.4 | Pending | 0% |\n340: | Phase 5: Runtime Config | T5.1, T5.2, T5.3 | Pending | 0% |\n341: | Phase 6: Concurrent Safety | T6.1, T6.2 | Pending | 0% |\n342: | Phase 7: Unit Tests | T7.1, T7.2, T7.3, T7.4, T7.5, T7.6 | Pending | 0% |\n343: | Phase 8: Integration & Validation | T8.1, T8.2, T8.3, T8.4 | Pending | 0% |\n344: \n345: **Total Progress: 0% Complete (0/24 tasks)**\n\n(End of file - total 345 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器 |\n| Module | `pkg/agentd` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Core Types & Constants (ST-1)\n\n- [ ] **T1.1**: Create `pkg/agentd/doc.go` with package documentation\n  - Package name: `agentd`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775868775802,"end":1775868775824}}}}
